{"questionId":"20902","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> defined by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></math>, for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>π</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>The following diagram shows the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math>.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" src=\"__IMG__/e94280b47888967880ffce9ea7a6ccd7f9d9909a.png\"></p>\n<p>The graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi></math> touches the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis at points <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math>, as shown. The shaded region is&nbsp;enclosed by the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> and the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis, between the points&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>A</mtext></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>B</mtext></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The right cone in the following diagram has a total surface area of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></math>, equal to the shaded&nbsp;area in the previous diagram.</p>\n<p>The cone has a base radius of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math>, height <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi></math>, and slant height <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>l</mi></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/26f8b695969a454bdb5f431f024eb73f7ba348da.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence, find the volume of the cone.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>valid attempt to find the height of the cone &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>e.g.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>h</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mtext>their</mtext><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>l</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>h</mi><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>12</mn></msqrt><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to use&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>π</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>h</mi></math>&nbsp;with their values substituted&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mfenced><msup><mn>2</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced><mfenced><msqrt><mn>12</mn></msqrt></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>volume</mtext><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msqrt><mn>12</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>8</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>8</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"20902","referenceCode":"21M.1.SL.TZ2.8d","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence, find the volume of the cone.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.1—3d space, volume, angles, distance, midpoints"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}